Step 1: Identify the Net Profit from the income statement.  
• Net Profit = 1,250,911.98

Step 2: Determine the beginning and ending Total Assets from the balance sheet.  
• Beginning Total Assets = 28,000,000.00  
• Ending Total Assets = 31,154,033.87

Step 3: Compute the Average Total Assets.  
• Average Total Assets = (28,000,000.00 + 31,154,033.87) / 2  
• Average Total Assets = 59,154,033.87 / 2  
• Average Total Assets = 29,577,016.935

Step 4: Calculate the Return on Assets (ROA).  
• ROA = (Net Profit / Average Total Assets) × 100%  
• ROA = (1,250,911.98 / 29,577,016.935) × 100%  
• ROA ≈ 0.04228 × 100%  
• ROA ≈ 4.23%

Thus, the ROA is approximately 4.23%.
